---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const personSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "@id": "https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/about/#founder",
  "name": "Costa Mavros",
  "givenName": "Costa",
  "familyName": "Mavros",
  "jobTitle": "Principal & Founder",
  "worksFor": {
    "@id": "https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/#business"
  },
  "description": "Costa Mavros is the principal and founder of Berwick Window Replacement, with 13 years of window replacement experience in Berwick."
};
---
<Layout
  title="About Berwick Window Replacement — Costa Mavros, principal & founder"
  description="Costa Mavros runs Berwick Window Replacement from Berwick — 13 years in window replacement. AGWA member. Meet the principal who quotes your job and runs the crew."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/about/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(personSchema)} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">About Berwick Window Replacement</span>
      <h1>Costa Mavros &mdash; <span class="accent">13 years</span> in window replacement across Berwick.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The principal who quotes your job, runs the crew, and answers his own phone after hours.
        AGWA member.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">The principal</span>
      <h2>How Berwick Window Replacement actually works.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width:65rem;">
        <p>Costa grew up in Berwick and has worked in window replacement here for 13 years. That matters more than the years on the ticket — the Berwick ground, the Berwick weather, the Berwick permitting process, and the Berwick suppliers are the things you only learn by doing the work in the place. There are tradies who can do window replacement anywhere; we only do it here, and we'd rather pass a job to a mate than do a job in a suburb we don't know.</p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">The Berwick side of it.</h3>
        <p>
          Berwick is not a market we read about; it's the market we live in. Costa
          volunteers at the Cardinia 4WD club track-clear weekends &mdash; the kind of detail that doesn't fit on a quote but does explain why the
          crew is on time, why the price doesn't drift, and why we'd rather pass a job to a mate than
          do work in a suburb we don't know. Every quote we issue is from someone you can put a face to.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2rem;">Credentials &amp; memberships.</h3>
        <ul style="margin-top:1rem;">
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">AGWA member</li><li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">AS 2047 compliant</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Public liability + workmanship insurance current; certificates available on request.</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Written, fixed-price quotes (no "from $X" range pricing).</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Same-person quoting and supervision &mdash; not a call-centre handoff.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="background:#f9fafb;">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">How we operate</span>
      <h2>What makes a Berwick Window Replacement job different.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width:65rem;">
        <h3>One person, start to finish.</h3>
        <p>
          Costa quotes the job and runs the crew that does the job. There is no
          handover, no junior estimator who lowballs the quote then upcharges on the day, and no
          third-party project manager who hasn't been on a job site in five years. If you ring at 7pm
          on a Wednesday, you get the person who's going to be on your property on Monday morning.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Written, fixed-price quotes.</h3>
        <p>
          Every quote we issue is all-inclusive &mdash; site assessment, weather risk, access risk,
          permit work if relevant. No "from $X" range pricing, no day-of-build surprise variations, no
          mid-job upsell. If a surprise lands on the dig that we did not allow for, it's our cost, not yours.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">A crew that stays the same.</h3>
        <p>
          The Berwick crew is the same five people it has been for four years. We don't sub work out
          to chase-cheap labour-hire crews, we don't put apprentices on a job without a registered
          tradesperson actively supervising, and we don't run a roster of fly-in workers. Continuity
          is what makes the work hold up at the 10-year mark.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="background:var(--ink);color:#fff;">
    <div class="section-inner" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 style="color:#fff;">Talk to Costa directly.</h2>
      <p style="opacity:0.85;max-width:50rem;margin:1rem auto 2rem;">
        Quotes are free, fixed-price and same-person. Phones go to Costa between
        7am and 7pm; after hours leave a message and we'll call back the next morning.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a fixed quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
